Rating: 3
My husband loves this dish...but with the following variation: in the olive oil (before you add the chicken), saute 4 cloves of garlic, thinly sliced and 2-4 birds' eye chilis, also thinly sliced. When the garlic has browned a little and turned crispy, remove it and add the chicken. Cook chicken until done, and at the last minute add back the garlic. The dish is hot and spicy, but boy is it good! I usually make a sauce to accompany it out of plain yogurt pureed with watercress, a little lemon juice, and salt.

