Rating: 3
I read some of the reviews of this recipe and decided to make some additions to the marinade, to give the chicken some extra flavor. I added another tablespoon of garlic, about a teaspoon of soy sauce, a little chicken broth and white wine, and probably a teaspoon (I hate exact measurements - I'd rather just approximate and give it what I think it needs) of crushed red pepper, and it turned out really well. It was flavorful, moist.... oh, I also used boneless/skinless breasts, and grilled them. I'd definitely make this again, but I'm pretty sure if I would have followed the recipe exactly it would have turned out bland. The recipe seems more like a guideline than anything - it was a nice opportunity to experiment a little, and not risk destroying the balance of the recipe.

